  "title": "Accessing Shared Network Drives and File Shares",
  "question": "How do I access shared network drives and file shares?",
  "answer": "Windows: Step 1: Click on the 'File Explorer' icon on your taskbar. Step 2: In the left pane, select 'This PC'. Step 3: Click on the 'Computer' tab at the top, then select 'Map network drive'. Step 4: Choose a drive letter from the dropdown menu. Step 5: In the 'Folder' field, enter the path to the shared drive (e.g., \\servername\sharename). Step 6: Check 'Reconnect at sign-in' if you want to access it automatically in the future, then click 'Finish'. macOS: Step 1: Open 'Finder' from your Dock. Step 2: In the menu bar, click on 'Go', then select 'Connect to Server'. Step 3: In the 'Server Address' field, enter the path to the shared drive (e.g., smb://servername/sharename). Step 4: Click 'Connect'. Step 5: If prompted, enter your network credentials (username and password). Step 6: Select the shared folder you want to access and click 'OK'. Now you can access the shared files from your Finder sidebar under 'Shared'."
}
